{
  "doc_id": "23516",
  "text": "The RNAi pathway plays important roles in silencing transposon and viruses in animal and plant cells and is thought to be a defense system against viruses and transposons [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Components of the RNAi pathway probably cleave viral dsRNA and degrade viral and transposon mRNAs. Consistent with this notion, many viral genomes are known to encode inhibitors of the RNAi pathway [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
